>>1cfefcf0-1fe3-4ef8-aa48-cf85c39a73bc
I think we've all played on some good servers over the years. I remember playing on an 8/tg/ server a few years ago that had about a hundred mods on it, it was great. We had the hardest time getting started because we spawned next to a desert village, but one of the mods introduced a mob that spawned more of itself when it detected you. They wound up overrunning the entire village, killing all the villagers there while we spent hours jumping from roof to roof, experimenting on them and trying to figure out a way to quarantine them.
We did wind up killing hundreds of them before we installed a wall around the entire village... and then we found out they can climb walls like spiders, so we had to dig a huge moat around the village, too. It was a grim and amazing experience that lasted about three days. Everything went well until the server died of inactivity - we had almost no faggots coming in and fucking around for shits and giggles. It was almost the ideal Minecraft experience.
